videos.description: After Seminoles QB Deondre Francois throws an incomplete pass, he is taken to the ground appearing to injure his shoulder. He is forced to leave the game.

videos.description: Stacy Coley 21 Yd pass from Brad Kaaya for a touchdown
videos.headline: Great catch extends Miami's lead

videos.description: Hurricanes QB Brad Kaaya tosses a 21-yard pass to WR Stacy Coley in the end zone but the referees rule it an incomplete pass. After review, it's determined that Coley was able to get his left foot down while securing the catch for a touchdown.

videos.headline: Referee overturns call for Miami TD
Miami extends lead on 51-yard field goal

videos.description: Florida State's Matthew Thomas ejected for targeting
videos.headline: Florida State's Matthew Thomas ejected for targeting

videos.description: Florida State linebacker Matthew Thomas is assessed a targeting penalty and ejected from the game after he hits Miami QB Brad Kaaya in the head.
videos.headline: FSU LB ejected for targeting

videos.description: Seminoles QB Deondre Francois tosses a 20-yard touchdown pass to WR Kermit Whitfield giving Florida State a 17-13 lead over the Miami.
videos.headline: FSU WR Whitfield catches a TD pass from Francois

videos.description: FSU QB Deondre Francois finds a wide-open Dalvin Cook for a 59-yard touchdown cutting the Seminoles' deficit to 13-10 against the Hurricanes.
videos.headline: Francois finds Cook for 59-yard TD

videos.description: Miami fans litter the field after targeting of Jamal Carter Sr. is upheld
videos.headline: Miami fans litter the field after targeting of Jamal Carter Sr. is upheld

videos.description: Hurricanes quarterback Brad Kaaya loses a tooth after taking a hard hit from FSU DB Matthew Thomas. An offensive lineman picks up the tooth and Kaaya takes it to the sidelines where he is checked for other possible tooth damage.

videos.headline: Hurricanes QB Brad Kaaya loses tooth after hit

videos.description: Going for the extra point to tie the game, Michael Badgley's kick is blocked and Florida State holds off Miami 20-19 for their seventh straight win over the Hurricanes.
videos.headline: FSU blocks an extra point, wins thriller over Miami
